node.title: Tropical low between Vanuatu and New Caledonia develops into a cyclone
node.description: The bad weather that has been affecting Vanuatu and New Caledonia has developed into a tropical cyclone.
node.content:
["The bad weather that has been affecting Vanuatu and New Caledonia has developed into a tropical cyclone.", "Tropical low TD08F, between New Caledonia and Vanuatu, is now a Category one Tropical Cyclone.", "", "
Tropical Cyclone Dovi, a category one cyclone between Vanuatu and New Caledonia. Photo: The Fiji Metrological Service
", "The Fiji Metrological Service has named the system, Dovi. It said the cyclone is moving East North-east at over 90km/h and intesifying.", "For Vanuatu, the system will bring heavy rainfalls with flash flooding expected over low lying areas, and areas close to river banks, including coastal flooding over the Vanuatu group tonight and continuing tomorrow.", "Very rough seas with heavy to phenomenal swells are expected over all Vanuatu waters.", "", "
Tracking map for Tropical Cyclone Dovi Photo: The Fiji Metrological Service
", "A marine strong wind warning is current for all coastal waters of Vanuatu.", "High Seas wind warning is also current for all open waters of Vanuatu. All sea going vessels are advised to take extra precautions.", "The Vanuatu Meteorology and Geo-Hazards Department has advised people listen to Radio Vanuatu and all other Radio outlets to get the latest warning update on this system."]
